03/05/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A total of 11,000 people danced hand in hand Monday (2 May) in a bid to enter the Guinness Book of Records by forming the world's longest chain dance. 
The event, led by Parliament Speaker Borislav Velikov, took place in front of St. 
Alexander Nevsky Cathedral in Sofia. 
President Georgi Parvanov was also among the participants. 
The dancers swayed for 30 minutes to the sound of Bulgarian folk music. 
(Trud - 03/05/05; bTV, Nova TV, Novinite - 02/05/05)
